<h2>Vision</h2>
<p><span id="internal-source-marker_0.3925700980736011">Roots and tubers improving the lives of the poor</span></p>
<h2>Mission</h2>
<p><span id="internal-source-marker_0.8555400993209332">The International Potato Center works with partners to achieve food security, well-being, and gender equity for poor people in root and tuber farming and food systems in the developing world. We do this through research and innovation in science, technology, and capacity strengthening.</span></p>
<h2><span>Core values</span></h2>
<p><b> </b></p>
<p><span id="internal-source-marker_0.8555400993209332"><b>Excellence: </b>We aim to excel in all we do.</span><br /><span><b>Dignity and respect:</b> We treat each other and our partners with dignity and respect.</span><br /><span><b>Empowerment:</b> We work to empower individuals at all levels for efficient, effective, and appropriate decision making.</span><br /><span><b>Integrity: </b>We remain honest, transparent, and accountable, individually and collectively, in what we say and do.</span><br /><span><b>Staff diversity:</b> We are committed to staff diversity and aspire to provide an equal opportunity working environment.</span><br /><span><b>Innovation and creativity:</b> We value innovation and creativity across our business.</span><br /><span><b>Partnership:</b> We actively participate in and encourage dynamic partnerships.</span></p>